data.story_headline: Career-High Day from McClanahan & Hubbard Lead Bobcats Past Cal State San Marcos
data.story_summary: SAN MARCOS, Calif. – Sterling McClanahan poured in 29 of his career-high 34 points in the second half as the University of California, Merced men's basketball team pulled away from Cal State San Marcos late, beating the Cougars 80-66 inside The Sports Center on Saturday afternoon.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Fall in Overtime to Cal State Monterey Bay
data.story_summary: SEASIDE, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team fell 89-83 in overtime to Cal State Monterey Bay on Thursday night.

data.story_headline: Women’s Basketball Unable to Overcome Fast Otters Start
data.story_summary: SEASIDE, Calif. — The University of California, Merced women's basketball team battled through an early Otters surge, but could not overcome the fast start by Cal State Monterey Bay, falling 73-62 on Thursday evening at The Kelp Bed.

data.story_headline: Women's Basketball Falls to Stanislaus State
data.story_summary: TURLOCK, Calif. — The University of California, Merced women's basketball team mounted a second-half surge but could not erase an early deficit, falling 66-58 to Stanislaus State on Saturday afternoon inside Ed & Bertha Fitzpatrick Arena.

data.story_headline: Men's Volleyball Sweeps La Sierra
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's volleyball team swept La Sierra 3-0 (25-14, 25-14, 25-18) on Saturday night inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Win Third Straight and Sweep Season Series with Stanislaus State
data.story_summary: TURLOCK, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team beat Stanislaus State for the second time in three days, beating the Warriors 68-64 on the backend of the home-and-home series on Saturday afternoon.

data.story_headline: UC Merced Beats Simpson in Four Sets to Start 2026 Campaign
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's volleyball team tallied 52 kills on a .415 hitting percentage to beat Simpson in four sets on Friday night, winning the season opener and Chris Carter's head coaching debut by set scores of 25-17, 25-19, 23-25, 25-12.

data.story_headline: UC Merced Wins Comeback Thriller Over Stanislaus State, 60-59
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team fought back from a second half double-digit deficit to beat Stanislaus State 60-59 on Thursday night inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Roll to 70-52 Win Over Stanislaus State
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. — The University of California, Merced women's basketball team established control in the opening minutes of the game and led by double-digits for nearly the final three quarters, defeating Stanislaus State 70-52 on Thursday evening at Greg and Cathie Hostetler Court.

data.story_headline: Women's Basketball Pulls Off Comeback Over San Francisco State, Bobcats Win 63-58
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced women's basketball team overcame a 15-point second half deficit to beat San Francisco State 63-58 on Saturday afternoon inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Two Bobcats Score 20+ In 92-77 Win Over San Francisco State
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team scored a season-high 92 points in a 92-77 win over San Francisco State on Saturday afternoon inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: UC Merced Comes Up Short Against No. 7 Cal State East Bay
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team fell 75-62 to seventh-ranked Cal State East Bay on Thursday night inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium. Cal State East Bay improved to 15-0 overall and 9-0 in the CCAA.

data.story_headline: Lukito Shines, Women’s Basketball Falls 90-89 to Cal State East Bay
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. — The University of California, Merced women's basketball team fell in a hard-fought 90-89 decision to Cal State East Bay on Thursday evening inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Men's Basketball Falls in Tightly Contested Game to Cal State LA, 76-73
data.story_summary: LOS ANGELES – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team fell short to Cal State LA 73-70 on Saturday afternoon.

data.story_headline: UC Merced Falls to Cal State LA
data.story_summary: LOS ANGELES – The University of California, Merced women's basketball team fell 96-75 to Cal State LA on Saturday afternoon.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Fall to Cal State Dominguez Hills
data.story_summary: CARSON, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team lost 92-73 to Cal State Dominguez Hills on Thursday night inside the Torodome.

data.story_headline: Women's Basketball Dominates CSUDH For First CCAA Win, 91-61
data.story_summary: CARSON, Calif. – The University of California, Merced women's basketball team caught fire offensively to win its first ever CCAA game, dominating Cal State Dominguez Hills 91-61 on Thursday night inside the Torodome.

data.story_headline: Women's Water Polo Announces 2026 Schedule
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. - The University of California, Merced women's water polo team has unveiled its 2026 schedule, featuring three multi-team events and eight WWPA matches. The home schedule is highlighted by a five-game homestand March 14-22.

data.story_headline: Trinidad Quiroz Signs With Necaxa Femenil
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – University of California, Merced women's soccer star Trinidad Quiroz has signed with Necaxa Femenil of Liga BBVA MX Femenil.

data.story_headline: Men’s Basketball Falls 86-80 to Cal State Monterey Bay
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team shot over 50% from the field and scored 80 points, but the Bobcats were unable to slow down the leagues highest scoring offense and fell 86-80 to Cal State Monterey Bay on Sunday afternoon inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Women's Basketball Falls to Cal State Monterey Bay
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced women's basketball team fell 61-48 to Cal State Monterey Bay on Sunday afternoon inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: UC Merced Edged by Cal State San Marcos
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team fell 62-57 to Cal State San Marcos on Friday night inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Fall 70-64 to Cal State San Marcos
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced women's basketball team dropped a 70-64 decision to Cal State San Marcos on Friday night inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Four Bobcats Named to CSC Academic All-District Team
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. - Taylor Crayne, Kyra Miller, Semiramis Tanasescu, and Yahaira Vazquez of the University of California, Merced women's volleyball team have earned College Sports Communicators Academic All-District honors.

data.story_headline: Men's Basketball Comes up Short to Cal State San Bernardino
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team had Cal State San Bernardino on the ropes, but the Bobcats were edged in the final seconds 61-60 on Sunday afternoon inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium

data.story_headline: Bobcats Battle to the End in 58-54 Loss to Cal State San Bernardino
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced women's basketball team battled back to take a lead inside the final minute, but Cal State San Bernardino answered with a clutch shot of their own and sank free throws to beat the Bobcats 58-54 on Sunday afternoon inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Fall to Cal Poly Pomona, 79-65
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced men's basketball team fell 79-65 to Cal Poly Pomona on Friday night inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Strong Defense Not Enough to Beat #15 Cal Poly Pomona
data.story_summary: MERCED, Calif. – The University of California, Merced women's basketball team played stifling defense but fell 53-40 to 15th-ranked Cal Poly Pomona on Friday night inside the Joseph Edward Gallo Gymnasium.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Downed by Cal Poly Humboldt
data.story_summary: ARCATA, Calif. – University of California, Merced women's basketball fell 94-55 in the final game of a program-long seven game road trip on Saturday afternoon inside Lumberjack Arena.

data.story_headline: Bobcats Excel Offensively to Earn First CCAA Win, 74-64 Over Cal Poly Humboldt
data.story_summary: ARCATA, Calif. - The University of California, Merced men's basketball team shot 56% from the floor to earn its first ever CCAA win, 74-64 at Cal Poly Humboldt on Saturday afternoon in Arcata.
